prints
```
[1, 2, 3] : Is not a valid triangle.
[1, 2, 8] : Is not a valid triangle.
[8, 8, 8] : Is a equilateral triangle.
[4, 8, 4] : Is not a valid triangle.
[4, 5, 7] : Is a scalene triangle.
[7, 7, 8] : Is an isoceles triangle.
[5, 3, -2] : Is not a valid triangle.

```
- first eliminate invalid triangles.
- Invalid triangles are
  - one or more sides &lt;= 0
  - any side &gt;= to the sum of the other two (which captures the first criteria)
- The rest are legal and evaluated by standard tests.  Order is important!
  -  first check for equilateral - all sides equal length
  -   then for isosceles - two sides equal length
  -   default to scalene. - no sides equal length
```	
	
public static String analyze(int a, int b, int c) {
	if (a &gt;= b + c || b &gt;= a + c || c &gt;= a + b){
		return &quot;Is not a valid triangle.&quot;;
	}

	if (a == b &amp;&amp; b == c) {
		return &quot;Is a equilateral triangle.&quot;;
	}
	
	if (a == b || b == c || a == c) {
		return &quot;Is an isoceles triangle.&quot;;
	}

	return &quot;Is a scalene triangle.&quot;;
}

