# Catch `IllegalArgumentException` from `Set.of`

The [`Set.of`][1] convenience method in Java 9+ creates a `Set` of an unspecified implementation when passed an array. If any duplicates are encountered while building this `Set`, an exception is thrown. You can trap for that `IllegalArgumentException` to know if the parts of your string are distinct or not.

We can get an array of the parts of your string by calling [`String#split`][2].

```java
